s fundamentally opposed to mediocrity as that which does not stand out or lacks distinctiveness; in the conjunctive sense, modern art turns to non-exceptional life in order to transform it-without forsaking its commonness-thereby producing exemplary forms of mediocrity that both represent the non-exceptional and, insofar as they stand outside the group they represent, are something other than mediocre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAesthetics in literature. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismx18th century. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aGerman literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804769983zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804769983423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804769983.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles